"You
could
not
have
visited
me!"
she
cried,
looking
aghast.
"No,
to
be
sure
you
could
not;
but
I
never
thought
of
that
before.
That
would
have
been
too
dreadful!
What
an
escape!
Dear
Miss
Woodhouse,
I
would
not
give
up
the
pleasure
and
honour
of
being
intimate
with
you
for
any
thing
in
the
world."
"Indeed,
Harriet,
it
would
have
been
a
severe
pang
to
lose
you;
but
it
must
have
been.
You
would
have
thrown
yourself
out
of
all
good
society.
I
must
have
given
you
up."
"Dear
me!
How
should
I
ever
have
borne
it!
It
would
have
killed
me
never
to
come
to
Hartfield
any
more!"
"Dear
affectionate
creature!
You
banished
to
Abbey
Mill
Farm!
You
confined
to
the
